<?xml version="1.0"?><h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><h:head><h:title>OSCE_Perform Immunization – OPV</h:title><model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0"><instance><data id="osce1_form" version="1.1"><intro><reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3/><step1/><step2/><step3/><step4/><step5/><step6/><step7/><step8/><step9/><step10/><step11/></intro><meta><instanceID/></meta></data></instance><bind nodeset="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step1" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step2" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step3" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step4" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step5" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step6" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step7" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step8" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step9" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step10" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step11" required="true()" type="string"/><bind jr:preload="uid" nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" readonly="true()" type="string"/></model></h:head><h:body class="pages"><group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/intro"><select1 appearance="label" ref="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3"><label> </label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step1"><label>Keeps the necessary items ready , vaccine carrier with OPV</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Check VVM on the vial and the expiry date before use. Discards the vaccine if the inner square is darker or has the same colour as the outer circle .</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Opens the dropper bottle by removing the cap and put the bottle on the foam in vaccine carrier to keep it cold.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>secures the dropper cap on the open vial.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Ask the mother to hold the child firmly, with the child lying on his back in her lap.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Open the child's mouth by stimulating the circumoral area using her little finger this makes the child's open mouth .</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Hold the dropper over the child's mouth at an angle of 45°. squeeze two drops of vaccine from the dropper on to the child's tongue.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Make sure the child swallows the vaccine. If it is spit out, give another dose.This step can be deleted as 6 weeks baby will swallow without spitting</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Put two drops directly in the mouth of the child. Take care that the dropper does not touch the mouth.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Put the dropper and vial on the foam in a vaccine carrier to keep them cold.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Documents in immunisation card and gives 4 key messages about immunisation. 
-Which vaccine was given and which disease does the vaccine protects against 
-When to come for next vaccination 
-Effects and side effects of immunisation and how to manage the same 
-Keeping immunisation card safe and bringing it on next visit.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>